<TD><FONT SIZE=-1>"</FONT><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">. . .God is love.
In this way, the love of God was revealed to us: God sent His only Son
into the world so that we might have life through Him. In this is love:
not that we have loved God, but that He loved us . . ."</FONT></B>
<BR><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">1 John 4:8-10</FONT></B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">"It is Christ, the last Adam, who fully
discloses man to himself and unfolds his noble calling by revealing the
mystery of the Father and the Father’s love." Gaudium et Spes, 22.</FONT></B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">Thus, in revealing man to himself, Christ
reveals that man is made for love, i.e. to cherish and to care for others.&nbsp;</FONT></B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">"For this is the message you have heard
from the beginning: we should love one another, . . ."</FONT></B>
<BR><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">1 John 3:11.</FONT></B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">The loving heart beats with the joys
of heaven.</FONT></B>
<BR><B><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">&nbsp;</FONT></B></TD>
</TR>
